{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1023,"text":"What if I told you that time has a race,"},{"time":5802,"text":"a race in the contemporary way\nthat we understand race"},{"time":8586,"text":"in the United States?"},{"time":10160,"text":"Typically, we talk about race\nin terms of black and white issues."},{"time":15546,"text":"In the African-American communities\nfrom which I come,"},{"time":18426,"text":"we have a long-standing\nmulti-generational joke"},{"time":21242,"text":"about what we call \"CP time,\""},{"time":23803,"text":"or \"colored people's time.\""},{"time":26259,"text":"Now, we no longer refer\nto African-Americans as \"colored,\""},{"time":29564,"text":"but this long-standing joke"},{"time":31350,"text":"about our perpetual lateness to church,"},{"time":33747,"text":"to cookouts, to family events"},{"time":35453,"text":"and even to our own funerals, remains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39116,"text":"I personally am a stickler for time."},{"time":41954,"text":"It's almost as if my mother,\nwhen I was growing up, said,"},{"time":44666,"text":"\"We will not be those black people.\""},{"time":46616,"text":"So we typically arrive to events\n30 minutes early."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50198,"text":"But today, I want to talk to you\nmore about the political nature of time,"},{"time":55099,"text":"for if time had a race,"},{"time":57042,"text":"it would be white."},{"time":59063,"text":"White people own time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62321,"text":"I know, I know."},{"time":64063,"text":"Making such \"incendiary statements\"\nmakes us uncomfortable:"},{"time":68614,"text":"Haven't we moved past the point\nwhere race really matters?"},{"time":72755,"text":"Isn't race a heavy-handed concept?"},{"time":75970,"text":"Shouldn't we go ahead\nwith our enlightened, progressive selves"},{"time":79041,"text":"and relegate useless concepts like race\nto the dustbins of history?"},{"time":83130,"text":"How will we ever get over racism\nif we keep on talking about race?"},{"time":89779,"text":"Perhaps we should lock up our concepts\nof race in a time capsule,"},{"time":93387,"text":"bury them and dig them up\nin a thousand years,"},{"time":96332,"text":"peer at them with the clearly\nmore enlightened,"},{"time":98724,"text":"raceless versions of ourselves\nthat belong to the future."},{"time":102497,"text":"But you see there,"},{"time":103815,"text":"that desire to mitigate the impact\nof race and racism shows up"},{"time":108430,"text":"in how we attempt to manage time,"},{"time":110768,"text":"in the ways we narrate history,"},{"time":112852,"text":"in the ways we attempt to shove\nthe negative truths of the present"},{"time":116022,"text":"into the past,"},{"time":117204,"text":"in the ways we attempt to argue\nthat the future that we hope for"},{"time":120284,"text":"is the present in which\nwe're currently living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123389,"text":"Now, when Barack Obama\nbecame President of the US in 2008,"},{"time":126555,"text":"many Americans declared\nthat we were post-racial."},{"time":130340,"text":"I'm from the academy"},{"time":131653,"text":"where we're enamored\nwith being post-everything."},{"time":134484,"text":"We're postmodern, we're post-structural,\nwe're post-feminist."},{"time":139373,"text":"\"Post\" has become\na simple academic appendage"},{"time":141829,"text":"that we apply to a range of terms"},{"time":143793,"text":"to mark the way we were."},{"time":146335,"text":"But prefixes alone don't have the power\nto make race and racism"},{"time":150511,"text":"a thing of the past."},{"time":152295,"text":"The US was never \"pre-race.\""},{"time":154939,"text":"So to claim that we're post-race when we\nhave yet to grapple with the impact"},{"time":158854,"text":"of race on black people,\nLatinos or the indigenous"},{"time":161776,"text":"is disingenuous."},{"time":164082,"text":"Just about the moment\nwe were preparing to celebrate"},{"time":166975,"text":"our post-racial future,"},{"time":168370,"text":"our political conditions became\nthe most racial they've been"},{"time":171349,"text":"in the last 50 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173429,"text":"So today, I want to offer to you\nthree observations,"},{"time":176986,"text":"about the past, the present\nand the future of time,"},{"time":180396,"text":"as it relates to the combating\nof racism and white dominance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184997,"text":"First: the past."},{"time":187802,"text":"Time has a history,"},{"time":189713,"text":"and so do black people."},{"time":191704,"text":"But we treat time as though\nit is timeless,"},{"time":194394,"text":"as though it has always been this way,"},{"time":196822,"text":"as though it doesn't have\na political history"},{"time":199135,"text":"bound up with the plunder\nof indigenous lands,"},{"time":201369,"text":"the genocide of indigenous people"},{"time":203342,"text":"and the stealing of Africans\nfrom their homeland."},{"time":206982,"text":"When white male European philosophers"},{"time":208882,"text":"first thought to conceptualize\ntime and history, one famously declared,"},{"time":213906,"text":"\"[Africa] is no historical\npart of the World.\""},{"time":218470,"text":"He was essentially saying"},{"time":220068,"text":"that Africans were people\noutside of history"},{"time":222459,"text":"who had had no impact on time"},{"time":224969,"text":"or the march of progress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227103,"text":"This idea, that black people\nhave had no impact on history,"},{"time":231572,"text":"is one of the foundational ideas\nof white supremacy."},{"time":235068,"text":"It's the reason that Carter G. Woodson\ncreated \"Negro History Week\" in 1926."},{"time":239926,"text":"It's the reason that we continue\nto celebrate Black History Month"},{"time":243065,"text":"in the US every February."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246780,"text":"Now, we also see this idea"},{"time":249154,"text":"that black people are people either\nalternately outside of the bounds of time"},{"time":253701,"text":"or stuck in the past,"},{"time":255233,"text":"in a scenario where,\nmuch as I'm doing right now,"},{"time":258132,"text":"a black person stands up and insists\nthat racism still matters,"},{"time":262282,"text":"and a person, usually white,"},{"time":264632,"text":"says to them,"},{"time":265822,"text":"\"Why are you stuck in the past?"},{"time":267782,"text":"Why can't you move on?"},{"time":270087,"text":"We have a black president."},{"time":272015,"text":"We're past all that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":274751,"text":"William Faulkner famously said,"},{"time":276984,"text":"\"The past is never dead."},{"time":279103,"text":"It's not even past.\""},{"time":281996,"text":"But my good friend\nProfessor Kristie Dotson says,"},{"time":285109,"text":"\"Our memory is longer than our lifespan.\""},{"time":289204,"text":"We carry, all of us,"},{"time":291530,"text":"family and communal\nhopes and dreams with us."},{"time":297080,"text":"We don't have the luxury\nof letting go of the past."},{"time":301986,"text":"But sometimes,"},{"time":303929,"text":"our political conditions are so troubling"},{"time":305938,"text":"that we don't know\nif we're living in the past"},{"time":308151,"text":"or we're living in the present."},{"time":310268,"text":"Take, for instance,\nwhen Black Lives Matter protesters"},{"time":312967,"text":"go out to protest unjust killings\nof black citizens by police,"},{"time":317012,"text":"and the pictures that emerge\nfrom the protest"},{"time":320137,"text":"look like they could have been\ntaken 50 years ago."},{"time":323795,"text":"The past won't let us go."},{"time":326696,"text":"But still, let us press our way\ninto the present."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331537,"text":"At present, I would argue"},{"time":333993,"text":"that the racial struggles\nwe are experiencing"},{"time":336354,"text":"are clashes over time and space."},{"time":340185,"text":"What do I mean?"},{"time":342300,"text":"Well, I've already told you\nthat white people own time."},{"time":345842,"text":"Those in power dictate\nthe pace of the workday."},{"time":349593,"text":"They dictate how much money\nour time is actually worth."},{"time":353973,"text":"And Professor George Lipsitz argues"},{"time":356139,"text":"that white people even dictate\nthe pace of social inclusion."},{"time":360074,"text":"They dictate how long\nit will actually take"},{"time":362854,"text":"for minority groups to receive the rights\nthat they have been fighting for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367315,"text":"Let me loop back to the past quickly\nto give you an example."},{"time":371101,"text":"If you think about\nthe Civil Rights Movement"},{"time":373268,"text":"and the cries of its leaders\nfor \"Freedom Now,\""},{"time":376225,"text":"they were challenging the slow pace\nof white social inclusion."},{"time":380317,"text":"By 1965, the year\nthe Voting Rights Act was passed,"},{"time":384369,"text":"there had been a full 100 years"},{"time":386023,"text":"between the end of the Civil War"},{"time":387890,"text":"and the conferral of voting rights\non African-American communities."},{"time":391060,"text":"Despite the urgency of a war,"},{"time":393299,"text":"it still took a full 100 years\nfor actual social inclusion to occur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398498,"text":"Since 2012,"},{"time":400457,"text":"conservative state legislatures\nacross the US have ramped up attempts"},{"time":404158,"text":"to roll back African-American\nvoting rights"},{"time":406371,"text":"by passing restrictive voter ID laws"},{"time":408870,"text":"and curtailing early voting opportunities."},{"time":411852,"text":"This past July, a federal court\nstruck down North Carolina's voter ID law"},{"time":415826,"text":"saying it \"... targeted African-Americans\nwith surgical precision.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":422605,"text":"Restricting African-American inclusion\nin the body politic"},{"time":426041,"text":"is a primary way that we attempt\nto manage and control people"},{"time":431057,"text":"by managing and controlling time."},{"time":434188,"text":"But another place that we see\nthese time-space clashes"},{"time":437780,"text":"is in gentrifying cities\nlike Atlanta, Brooklyn,"},{"time":441272,"text":"Philadelphia, New Orleans\nand Washington, DC --"},{"time":444763,"text":"places that have had\nblack populations for generations."},{"time":448411,"text":"But now, in the name\nof urban renewal and progress,"},{"time":451727,"text":"these communities are pushed out,"},{"time":453738,"text":"in service of bringing them\ninto the 21st century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456904,"text":"Professor Sharon Holland asked:"},{"time":460176,"text":"What happens when a person\nwho exists in time"},{"time":463867,"text":"meets someone who only occupies space?"},{"time":468897,"text":"These racial struggles"},{"time":470516,"text":"are battles over those\nwho are perceived to be space-takers"},{"time":474120,"text":"and those who are perceived\nto be world-makers."},{"time":478041,"text":"Those who control the flow\nand thrust of history"},{"time":481054,"text":"are considered world-makers\nwho own and master time."},{"time":485195,"text":"In other words: white people."},{"time":488270,"text":"But when Hegel famously said that Africa\nwas no historical part of the world,"},{"time":492399,"text":"he implied that it was merely\na voluminous land mass"},{"time":494928,"text":"taking up space\nat the bottom of the globe."},{"time":497520,"text":"Africans were space-takers."},{"time":500528,"text":"So today, white people continue to control\nthe flow and thrust of history,"},{"time":504835,"text":"while too often treating black people\nas though we are merely taking up space"},{"time":509402,"text":"to which we are not entitled."},{"time":511710,"text":"Time and the march of progress\nis used to justify"},{"time":515681,"text":"a stunning degree of violence\ntowards our most vulnerable populations,"},{"time":520120,"text":"who, being perceived as space-takers\nrather than world-makers,"},{"time":525219,"text":"are moved out of the places\nwhere they live,"},{"time":527560,"text":"in service of bringing them\ninto the 21st century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531868,"text":"Shortened life span according to zip code\nis just one example of the ways"},{"time":536022,"text":"that time and space cohere\nin an unjust manner"},{"time":538773,"text":"in the lives of black people."},{"time":540973,"text":"Children who are born\nin New Orleans zip code 70124,"},{"time":545518,"text":"which is 93 percent white,"},{"time":547470,"text":"can expect to live a full 25 years longer"},{"time":550723,"text":"than children born\nin New Orleans zip code 70112,"},{"time":555002,"text":"which is 60 percent black."},{"time":558036,"text":"Children born in Washington, DC's\nwealthy Maryland suburbs"},{"time":562184,"text":"can expect to live a full 20 years longer"},{"time":565314,"text":"than children born\nin its downtown neighborhoods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569672,"text":"Ta-Nehisi Coates argues"},{"time":572380,"text":"that, \"The defining feature\nof being drafted into the Black race"},{"time":578044,"text":"is the inescapable robbery of time.\""},{"time":581698,"text":"We experience time discrimination,"},{"time":583514,"text":"he tells us,"},{"time":584765,"text":"not just as structural,"},{"time":586269,"text":"but as personal:"},{"time":587744,"text":"in lost moments of joy,"},{"time":589592,"text":"lost moments of connection,"},{"time":591832,"text":"lost quality of time with loved ones"},{"time":594353,"text":"and lost years of healthy quality of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600009,"text":"In the future, do you see black people?"},{"time":604524,"text":"Do black people have a future?"},{"time":608389,"text":"What if you belong\nto the very race of people"},{"time":610643,"text":"who have always been pitted against time?"},{"time":614325,"text":"What if your group is the group\nfor whom a future was never imagined?"},{"time":620091,"text":"These time-space clashes --"},{"time":621811,"text":"between protesters and police,"},{"time":624376,"text":"between gentrifiers and residents --"},{"time":626770,"text":"don't paint a very pretty picture"},{"time":628791,"text":"of what America hopes\nfor black people's future."},{"time":632390,"text":"If the present is any indicator,"},{"time":634128,"text":"our children will be under-educated,"},{"time":636203,"text":"health maladies will take their toll"},{"time":638585,"text":"and housing will continue\nto be unaffordable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642092,"text":"So if we're really ready\nto talk about the future,"},{"time":645138,"text":"perhaps we should begin\nby admitting that we're out of time."},{"time":649994,"text":"We black people\nhave always been out of time."},{"time":653265,"text":"Time does not belong to us."},{"time":655413,"text":"Our lives are lives of perpetual urgency."},{"time":658633,"text":"Time is used to displace us,"},{"time":661189,"text":"or conversely, we are urged\ninto complacency"},{"time":664223,"text":"through endless calls to just be patient."},{"time":667985,"text":"But if past is prologue,"},{"time":670461,"text":"let us seize upon the ways in which\nwe're always out of time anyway"},{"time":673738,"text":"to demand with urgency"},{"time":675410,"text":"freedom now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677767,"text":"I believe the future is what we make it."},{"time":680646,"text":"But first, we have to decide\nthat time belongs to all of us."},{"time":685817,"text":"No, we don't all get equal time,"},{"time":688544,"text":"but we can decide that the time\nwe do get is just and free."},{"time":692586,"text":"We can stop making your zip code\nthe primary determinant"},{"time":695255,"text":"of your lifespan."},{"time":697024,"text":"We can stop stealing learning time\nfrom black children"},{"time":699768,"text":"through excessive use\nof suspensions and expulsions."},{"time":702848,"text":"We can stop stealing time\nfrom black people"},{"time":704941,"text":"through long periods\nof incarceration for nonviolent crimes."},{"time":708947,"text":"The police can stop\nstealing time and black lives"},{"time":711967,"text":"through use of excessive force."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715177,"text":"I believe the future is what we make it."},{"time":718424,"text":"But we can't get there\non colored people's time"},{"time":722463,"text":"or white time"},{"time":724415,"text":"or your time"},{"time":726251,"text":"or even my time."},{"time":728981,"text":"It's our time."},{"time":731063,"text":"Ours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732359,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733540,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}